name: AZ KIDZ PRESCHOOL/ DAYCARE, LLC
details:
Az Kidz recognizes that each child is an individual; that all children are creative; and that all children need to succeed. Therefore, Az Kidz respects the
individual needs of all children; fosters a caring and creative environment;
and emphasizes the social, emotional, physical, and intellectual
development of each child.

name: AZ KIDZ PRESCHOOL/DAYCARE, L.L.C.
details: Relocated on 650 WEST COMBS ROAD

name: BEACON LEARNING CENTER
details: Beacon Learning Center extends a warm welcome to all parents and their children who are entering our program. It is our hope that the learning and childcare experience will be happy and helpful for all

name: BRIGHT HORIZONS AT DOWNTOWN PHOENIX
details: Part of the Bright Horizons family of top-quality child care centers, Bright Horizons at Downtown Phoenix recognizes the positive result of supporting a lifelong love of learning. We offer high-quality care and education - places that allow parents to go to work knowing their children are happy, safe and well cared for, and where children move to the elementary years socially prepared, excited to learn, and well-versed in the language, math and science skills they'll need to succeed. Explore our website to learn more!

name: BRIGHTER ANGELS LEARNING CENTER CENTRAL, L.L.C.
details:
Welcome to our center! A child is a unique individual at Brighter Angels
Learning Center environment respects the child's unique developmental needs.
We encourage children to express their creativity and we focus on
opportunities for success. We encourage children to think about and reflect
on each decision they make, thus developing their problem solving skills,
creativity and excitement about learning areas are organized to provide
hands-on activities and to encourage children to problem-solve.

name: BRILLIANT SCHOLARS PRESCHOOL
details: Brilliant Scholars Preschool is an academically oriented, year-long school serving 1 to 5 aged students.   We strive to create an environment that will grow your child to be passionate for learning.

name: CAURUS EXPLORERS, L.L.C.
details: Our students start the day in a happy, nurturing environment. They learn by creating, discovering and exploring curriculum that is often connected to their personal interests. This approach allows a love of learning to flourish. See what a day at Caurus looks like.

name: CHAMPION CHANDLER PRESCHOOL
details: Champion Schools is powerful learning community for ALL students, regardless of their educational backgrounds. Our learning environment includes many opportunities to work collaboratively. We use common core, project based learning and utilize the community as a laboratory for students to have hands-on experiences. These types of learning activities activate the imagination, stimulate critical thinking and develop problem-solving skills. We believe in every student’s natural desire to learn and want to bring ALL of our students into the educational mainstream by the end of middle school.

name: CLUB ELEVATE
details: Club Elevate is an extension of the school day, focusing on discipleship, homework help, and enrichment. Registration is required.

name: DARKAYNU - TUCSON JEWISH MONTESSORI
details: Our focus is honoring the path of every child, with practical life skills and Jewish learning integrated into the Montessori system. King Solomon advises us in Proverbs 22:6 to “educate the child in the course of his path; even when he will be old he will not depart from it.” King Solomon’s direction is exemplified in the Montessori method of guiding each child individually. This is an important part of our objective to combine the best of Montessori with the values of our Jewish heritage for both general and Judaic subjects.

name: DISCOVERY LEARNING CENTER AND CHILD CARE
details: Discovery Learning Center and Child Care is now taking new child enrollments with no registration fees. We are open 24/7 and accept children from from the age of 1 year old up to 12 years old. We offer a pre-school program and include breakfast, lunch, snack and dinner at no extra cost. We provide a safe and fun learning environment that your child will enjoy. Come on in and take a look for yourself, we will be more than happy to assist you!

name: EARLY EDUCATION COOPERATIVE PRESCHOOL
details: Since 1961, the Early Education Cooperative Preschool (EECP) has provided a quality education program to Valley children and their families.

name: FLAGSTAFF YMCA - WEITZEL'S PUENTE DE HOZHO BILINGUAL MAGNET SCHOOL
details: Puente de Hózhó (PdH) Elementary School is a trilingual language school located in Flagstaff, Arizona and is a part of the Flagstaff Unified School District. PdH is a "dual-language school" and is comprised of a Navajo Immersion Language Program and a Spanish-English Bilingual Program. We serve students from Kindergarten through 5th-grade, but a 6-12 International Baccalaureate Continuum is being established to compliment PdH's programming. Featured in the Harvard Education Review for "best practices" for culturally sustaining and revitalizing teaching, PdH holds a radical belief in the potential of children, culture, and language in a local, regional, national, and international context. Consequently, PdH is also proud to call itself an International Baccalaureate Candidate School in addition to our stated vision, mission, and goals

name: FRANKLIN PHONETIC PRIMARY SCHOOL SUNNYSLOPE PRESCHOOL
details: The founders of Franklin Phonetic Primary School have always believed that it is important to encourage and enable students to successfully use higher level thinking skills. Today’s knowledge is growing at an exponentially rapid rate. Unlike schools of the previous century, memorization of rote facts and figures will not be enough to gain academic success. Instead students must learn to collect, interpret, evaluate and understand information. They must be able to critically evaluate and intellectually process the high amounts of information and data that are presented to them on an ever continuing basis.

name: FUN PLACE CHILDCARE & PRESCHOOL
details: Hi, my name is Ruth Saenz-Perez, more affectionately known as Mrs. Ruth by my kids, and I am the owner of Fun Place Childcare & Preschool. I'm really excited that you decided to visit my page! Choosing a daycare center for your littles can be both exciting and daunting. You want only the best for them, and so do I.  As a committed mother of 4, I am very family oriented and blessed to have their love and support.  Prior to expanding into the center I ran Fun Place from my home for 12 years, where my reputation grew along with my waiting list.  I was encouraged to get licensed and open a center by many, and prepared to do so once my youngest Daughter was of school age. I obtained an associates degree in business and my education in early childhood development is ongoing. After being at home for 12 years I was excited to get back to work and expanded Fun Place in November of 2016. Pictured above are myself and the 10 kids from my home daycare that joined me in opening the center.  So if you are looking for a safe, nurturing, positive and fun learning environment then look no further Fun Place has your back.  I look forward to meeting you!

name: GATEWAY COMMUNITY COLLEGE CHILDREN'S LEARNING CENTER - MONTECITO
details: The Children's Learning Center is located on the north side of the Washington Campus and a new location on Montecito and 7th Street. Childcare services are available for students and employees. Flexible scheduling is offered by our trained, caring staff. To qualify, children must be ages 2 through 12, fully potty trained

name: GIGGLE AND GROW PRESCHOOL & CHILD CARE
details: At Giggle and Grow, our mission is to make a positive difference in the life of every child by partnering with parents to provide an environment that is safe, nurturing, educational and individualized. With cameras in every classroom and a secure internet viewing service available to parents at all times, Giggle and Grow Child Care offers parents a sense of security unlike any other. This, in addition to dedicated, well-trained staff and a safe, stimulating environment, make Giggle and Grow Child Care the best choice for children and parents. At Giggle and Grow Child Care, we focus on the needs of very young children. We pride ourselves on being aware of the very latest in research and development in regards to early childhood education. We use this information to develop a preschool curriculum that is age appropriate in all classrooms.

name: GREATER PHOENIX URBAN LEAGUE HEAD START - BRET TARVER
details: We believe that ALL children can learn.  We strive to meet the needs by providing a researched-based early childhood curriculum, promoting high standards and realistic expectations to ensure success for ALL children, and modeling positive learning attitudes and values.Collectively, students are encouraged to make choices, follow daily routines, interact appropriately with peers, and accept responsibility for their actions. In the final analysis, the effectiveness or our preschool is assessed on the basis of the continuous progress (social, emotional, cognitive, and physical development) of our children.We provide a warm, inviting climate that enables children and families to enjoy their school experiences where parents are fully engaged in the teaching and learning role.

name: GREATER PHOENIX URBAN LEAGUE HEAD START-BYRON BARRY
details: The overall philosophy of the Greater Phoenix Urban League Head Start program is to provide a high quality, comprehensive program and services to children and their families in an effort to promote school readiness by enhancing cognitive, social, and emotional development. The program strives to empower families with support and resources to be the first teachers of their children and to enable them to meet their personal goals.

name: GREATER PHOENIX URBAN LEAGUE HEAD START-MOYA
HAPPY KIDS CHILD CARE CENTER I I
JOYFUL NOISE LEARNING CENTER
details: We're a loving and fun family oriented Center

name: KCE CHAMPIONS, L.L.C.
details: Inside your child lives a scientist, an artist, a teacher, a physician, a CEO. That’s why we designed our curriculum to bring out the best in your children and help them develop stronger problem-solving, teamwork, leadership, and life skills. Our teachers inspire children to follow their curiosity across a breadth of subjects— creative arts, math and construction, library time, puzzles and games, and science—to foster mental, physical, social, and emotional growth

name: KCE CHAMPIONS, L.L.C. AT BELL CANYON
details: Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.

name: KIDS FOREVER PRINCE CENTER
details: Many experts agree that all children should have some sort of group experience before they enter kindergarten. Music and gymnastics classes are wonderful, but preschools excel at teaching kids to be students.

name: KIDS LEARNING CENTERS ALGODON, L.L.C.
details: Kids Incorporated Child Care of Arizona encourages the natural curiosity of your child and uses it to help them to grow and to reach their full potential.

name: KIDSPARK
details: Our open, “no walls” floor plan gives children freedom of movement to choose the activity area that most interests them, and it allows continuous teacher observation. Without walls blocking visibility, parents can always see the exciting activities their children are engaged in at KidsPark. This ensures a safe and secure environment.

name: KINDER PREP ACADEMY
details: Kinder Prep Academy provides a quality, nurturing environment that will prepare children emotionally, socially and academically to enter Kindergarten.

name: LIFEPRINTS CHILDCARE
details: At Lifeprints learning center, we strive to create an environment where children are given the opportunity to explore their academic and individual potential.

name: LIL' EINSTEINS ACADEMY
details: Lil’ Einsteins Academy exists to provide a safe, developmentally appropriate environment for preschool and school age children. Our focus is to provide a stimulating early care and education experience which promotes each child’s social, emotional, physical and cognitive development. Our goal is to instill the love of learning and encourage children’s desire to be life-long learners under the guidance of qualified teachers.

name: LITTLE GENIUSES CHILDCARE CENTER
details: Little Geniuses Child Care Center objective is to provide high quality early childhood education to your child.  We go above and beyond to provide the ultimate in care for your child.  We are passionate about the growth of your children intellectually, emotionally and socially.  Our goal is to assist in developing a lifetime love of learning.

name: LITTLE TREASURES CHILD CARE
details: Little Treasures is a family business. Our goal is to provide families a safe and fun environment for their Little Treasures while they attend their daily activities. We want to make sure all of our parents feel comfortable droping off their children, knowing that they will have a fantastic day at the center.

name: LITTLE WONDERS LEARNING
details: Little Wonders Learning is more than a daycare. It is home. From the moment you walk through our doors, you are family. And, we will strive to make sure that you feel welcomed and for you to know how much we will love and care for your children. We don't want to be just a place to drop your children, we want to be the home that you trust to nuture the growth and education of your most precious treasures.  From our beginnings as an in home childcare to where we have grown to now, one thing has never changed: your child is our only priority!

name: LIVING HOPE CHRISTIAN CHILDCARE CENTER
details: At Living Hope we focus on the whole child: mind, body and spirit in a Christ centered environment. Our focus is to provide a stimulating early childcare and preschool experience which will ensure your child’s school readiness while we encourage the values and character qualities you teach at home, helping your child to love others and experience God’s love.

name: LOVABLE KIDS KARE
details: Ever since 2008, Lovable Kids Kare, LLC has been providing students with a rich and a diverse learning environment. Our unparalleled teaching methods help to launch students into the successful future they have always dreamed of. Lovable Kids Kare, LLC is located in Phoenix, Az. We encourage both staff and students alike to grow, learn and create each passing day.

name: M.P.A. -  CHANDLER L.L.C.

Maxwell Preschool Academy is committed to providing a developmentally age appropriate learning experience for each child.
Our staff is highly qualified and brings years of experience to the classroom.
Each day is filled with fun and exciting opportunities to help your child develop social skills, emotional skills, cognitive skills, and physical skills.
We would love having the honor to provide our services to you and your children. We have openings and are accepting new applications so to get started please contact a director at a location near you.
We believe in the potential of every child because their accomplishments are our greatest reward.
At Maxwell Preschool Academy we recognize the importance of a well-balanced education foundation. We know that parental peace of mind is priceless and that inspired teachers can inspire children to make the world their classroom.  
With the experience and background of the founders of Maxwell Preschool Academy we wish to assist parents in understanding the developmental stages of their child so they may contribute to their growth enrichment.

name: MIA PRESCHOOL & CHILDCARE, L.L.C.

name: MIRAMONTE DAY SCHOOL
details: Miramonte uses a contemporary Child Development philosophy of education, programs are designed to encourage physical, intellectual, social and emotional growth in young children. The school uses a combination of the best curriculums in early childhood education; such as, Reggio Emilia, Creative Curriculum, Arizona Standard Cores, Montessori, etc… We believe this philosophy of education teaches independence, responsibility, self-discipline and cognitive development at the child’s own pace, stressing the uniqueness of each child. Parents are involved through observation and daily parent/teacher interaction.

name: MIRO INTERNATIONAL PRESCHOOL
details: Welcome to Miró International Preschool. We are a boutique preschool with family values teaching in Spanish! Our team of qualified and experienced staff, supporting children in gaining independence and fulfilling their potential in a safe, caring and stimulating environment; Miró International Preschool aims to provide a happy, caring and secure environment, through the seven areas of learning: personal, social and emotional development, communication and language, literacy, mathematics, expressive arts and design, understanding of the world and physical development. We absolutely believe that joining our preschool your kid will be experiencing a unique and wonderful learning process in a wonderful place.

name: MUSLIM COMMUNITY CENTER OF TUCSON
details: Welcome to MCCT  We support justice, family values, honesty, truthfulness, mercy for the young, care for the old, and charity for the poor, upholding Islamic etiquettes and values; following the steps of our Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him)

name: N.A.C.O.G. - BEAVER CREEK HEAD START
details: Head Start has been a part of northern Arizona for over thirty years. The Northern Arizona Council of Governments (NACOG) administers the Program that has a service area of 27,000 square miles and includes the four counties of Apache, Navajo, Coconino, and Yavapai. The Program serves children zero to five years old who meet the required income guidelines. NACOG uses several program options to provide Preschool and Early Head Start services in 28 Northern Arizona communities on behalf of 1613 children.

name: NINA'S FAMILY CHILDCARE AT PARK LEE
PAIDEIA PRESCHOOL SOUTH MOUNTAIN, LLC
details: We combine our whole-child curriculum with ample physical play (body), rigorous exploratory academics (mind), emotional and social interaction (heart) and self-reflection on principles of character (spirit) to promote healthy development and learning. Paideia preschool introduces our scholars to “The Leader In Me – 7 Habits” culture of Paideia Academy

name: PRIMROSE SCHOOL OF GILBERT AT SANTAN
details: We’re a national family of accredited early education and care schools serving infants through kindergarten, after-schoolers, their families and communities. With our Balanced Learning® approach, we help empower children to reach their full potential by nurturing curiosity, confidence, creativity and compassion.

name: SAN PEDRO VALLEY DAYCARE AND PRESCHOOL
details: The center offers working San Pedro Valley parents and those who need occasional help with a child care option. We modify what we do based on the needs of the family; some parents need care for their children Monday-Friday, all day, others some days, others after school. Some parents need early drop off, others ride the school bus after their school to attend the homework club.   Some attend Pre School in the morning, afternoon or both and even others complete on line schooling using our computers and while being supervised by our staff.

name: SARRC COMMUNITY SCHOOL - TEMPE CAMPUS
details: An inclusive preschool program that provides intensive, ABA-based programming for children with ASD and high-quality early childhood education for typically developing children. Children 18 months to 5 years old experience important social and academic fundamentals to ensure kindergarten readiness.

name: SHELLIE'S EARLY START LEARNING CENTER #2
details: To strive to be a positive and intergrating influence in each child's process of self identification. We will create and environment within eachchild's process of self worth and mental attitude that fosters educational excellence. to help promote the skills of making choice and rational decisions as they relate to themselves and others.

name: ST. FRANCIS OF ASSISI SCHOOL
details: Saint Francis of Assisi Catholic School is committed to educational excellence within the traditions of the Roman Catholic faith. We, along with parental support, educate our students to grow in the image and likeness of God, so they may become confident leaders in service to others as well as beacons of hope for all.

name: ST. MARK LITTLE TOTS CHILDREN CENTER
details: St. Mark Little Tots Children's Center is to foster a safe learning environment for the  whole child, centered in Christ. We strive to create an environment where one will grow by discovering his or her own world through fun and organized play, creative lessons, and surroundings filled with faith, family, and friends. Through the guidance of the Holy Spirit we strive to build the Kingdom of God through the eyes of the children.

name: TREE OF LIFE PRESCHOOL ACADEMY, L.L.C.
details: At Tree of Life Preschool Academy we will ensure the academic, emotional, social and developmental success of each child in a loving, creative and safe environment. We will empower each child to use their unique gifts, learning styles, and strengths for a successful future as students, citizens and community members.

name: U3 ACADEMY CHILDCARE CENTER L.L.C.
details: U3 Academy Child Care is located in Sierra Vista, Arizona. Come tour at our brand new facility!

name: VAL VISTA ACADEMY
details: Val Vista Academy is in its sixth year,  a Kindergarten- Eighth Grade Charter/Public School, "Where Children Are the Priority". Our goals of: high parent satisfaction and increasing student performance are at the heart of our mission.Our desire is to partner with parents in the pursuit of excellence for all students. We offer a well-rounded core academic program which stresses literacy and a standards based approach to education.Our Ball Charter Curriculum is aligned to Arizona Common Core State Standards. As you read through our web-site please think of how you can contribute to the growth and maturity of Val Vista Academy. We look forward to the opportunity to offer our students an exciting, rigorous and enjoyable set of educational and life experiences.

name: WHIZ KIDZ PRESCHOOL - SCOTTSDALE
details: We place the highest importance on your child’s development, safety, and that they feel loved and appreciated. The parents of the children that we enroll in our preschool program consider us to be among the best preschools in the Phoenix area for value, personalized attention, discipline, and award-winning preschool curriculum.

name: WIGGLES AND GIGGLES, L.L.C.
details: Every child is unique and we believe that success and growth come from encouragement and praise. Our teachers focus on building every child’s self esteem and confidence through positive feedback and rewarding good behavior and academics.

name: Y.M.C.A. AT DESERT CHRISTIAN ELEMENTARY
details: The goal of the Preschool Program is for our young children to know, love, and follow Jesus Christ, while developing an academic foundation for the elementary years ahead. Providing a close teacher child relationship within a happy Christian environment is our primary focus.

name: A.E.S.D. #68 - CORDOVA MIDDLE SCHOOL
details: We share with the community the responsibility to educate the whole child. To help students dream big, we will create a rich, varied selection of learning experiences. So that students believe it, we will establish an environment that nurtures positive self-esteem and generates creativity for all students. We will also foster a cooperative connection between all stakeholders through the use of technological resources and personal accountability so that all students have the opportunity to achieve it.

name: B.U.S.D.#9 - BOBCAT CITIZEN PRESCHOOL
details: Welcome to Benson Primary School, home of the proud Bobcat Citizen.  We prepare students to be “On Track for Tomorrow!”  Everything we do at Benson Primary School aligns to our motto, mission, and guiding principles and positively impacts the life of every child.  Our success begins with happy children and outstanding personnel!

name: C.S.D.#83 - CARTWRIGHT EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
details: At Cartwright we take our motto seriously, “Learning for all. Every child, every school, every day." We don’t just prepare students for high school. We prepare them for college, careers and the world. That’s what it means to provide a world-class education. Cartwright School District #83 proudly serves the Maryvale community.

name: C.U.S.D. #24 - CANYON DE CHELLY
details: CDC serves students and families in grades K-6 who desire academically rigorous coursework and development of practical skills for life applications. Courses are not only academically but technology driven.

name: F.U.S.D.#1 - SAN TAN HEIGHTS HAWKS
details: We are committed to developing future leaders with the character and academic excellence necessary to meet the challenges in life .

name: K.E.S.D.#28 - C.I. WAGGONER ELEMENTARY
details: The Waggoner Way is a school-wide program, Positive Behavior Interventions and Supports (PBIS) The Waggoner Way is a school-wide program based on the Positive Behavior Interventions and Supports (PBIS) framework. The staff has worked closely together to develop The Waggoner Way, which matches the principles of PBIS in a way that fits the goals, mission and culture of C.I. Waggoner Elementary School.

name: L.E.S.D.#59 - PASEO POINT KIDS KLUB
details: The Kids Klub Program is a licensed program of the Laveen Elementary School District and is supported solely by fees collected from registered participants. This program offers carefully planned, well-supervised activities for children in grades kindergarten through sixth. The many opportunities offered through the program are designed to interest your child and to foster his/her emotional well-being and social, physical, and critical thinking skills.

name: M.S.D.#18 - WILDKITTEN DEN
details: Wildkitten Den will provide daycare, preschool and before and after school care to children 6 weeks and older. This facility will operate as part of the Morenci Early Learning Center which currently serves non-school aged children. We are excited to expand on the education and care currently provided.

name: M.U.S.D.#6 - GLADDEN FARMS L.E.A.P./ PRESCHOOL
details: Early Childhood Education (ECE) Centers are tuition funded and licensed early learning facilities available forPSFlower.png four and five year old children the year prior to entering kindergarten. Children participate in small/large group activities as well as enrichment learning activities that promote development in the arts and large motor skills. The Arizona Early Learning Standards are followed to prepare children for kindergarten.

name: MAINE CONSOLIDATED SCHOOL DISTRICT #10
details: Maine Consolidated School District is dedicated to achieving educational excellence for all. Through high expectations, the development of lifelong learning habits, promoting active parental involvement, and quality professional development; we enable our students to embrace the change, growth, and opportunities for achievement in the diverse world of their future, and thereby become productive and successful citizens.

name: P.U.S.D.#11 - PIONEER ECCEL
details: Pioneer has a reputation of academic greatness, a supportive family culture and collaboration. It is my intent to continue to carry out these important traditions and practices, firmly establishing a culture focused on student learning and high expectations where students are taught to be SAFE, CARING, RESPECTFUL AND RESPONSIBLE.

name: P.U.S.D.#11 - SAHUARO RANCH KIDZONE

Through this program, K-8 students are able to learn and interact in a safe, caring environment. The KidZone Mission is to provide a physically and emotionally safe environment where children can participate in engaging activities and build positive relationships.

name: RIVERSIDE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL DISTRICT #2
details: We are excited for parents, students, and the community to become part of the Riverside family; a community school district where students are provided with an advanced curriculum by master teachers and highly qualified staff. We invite you to use our district Web site to learn more about our wonderful programs, our state of the art schools, and our many academic achievements.

name: S.O.C.U.S.D. - SEDONA INTEGRATED PRESCHOOL
details: We will provide your child with a warm, caring and safe environment to ensure your child can reach their maximum potential. We are trained to help your child develop and build on skills through developmentally appropriate activities. Your child will participate in a variety of experiential and play activities that will promote cognitive (thinking), language, pre-literacy, gross/fine motor skill and social skills.

name: T.U.S.D.#1 - BANKS PRESCHOOL PROGRAM
details: The preschool at Banks Elementary School is an inclusive program for typically developing and special needs children ages 3-4. There is a teacher and two highly-qualified classroom aides. The program focuses on academic, social, emotional and physical development based on the student's ability. Children are placed into this program through CHILD FIND
wednesday hour: Staff Planning and Professional Development day

name: T.U.S.D.#1 - BLOOM PRESCHOOL PROGRAM
details: Bloom knows the importance of literacy and biliteracy. We want our students to be successful in tomorrow’s job markets. Bilingual skills are highly valued, and the key to being bilingual is starting early. Bloom now offers a Spanish immersion, Two-Way Dual Language kindergarten class. We will be expanding the program to other grades over the next several years, eventually to all grade levels.

name: T.U.S.D.#1 - HOLLADAY PRESCHOOL PROGRAM
details: We provide leadership skills to all of our students. We are committed to instilling leadership principles in our students that will serve them now and into the future.

name: V.U.S.D.#20 - COPPER RIDGE ENRICHMENT PROGRAM
details: Our mission is to provide a safe, nurturing, and supportive learning environment that is dedicated to meet the individual needs and promote growth in all students. Through a community partnership, we will ensure academic achievement through engaging and interactive instruction to instill a love of learning in our students.

name: 4CS CLOVERDALE PRESCHOOL
details: 4Cs Cloverdale Preschool is a child centered program that celebrates diversity and embraces family and community involvement. Our program cultivates the cognitive, physical, and social-emotional development of young children through hands-on, process-oriented activities that support children’s natural abilities.

name: A PLACE TO GROW
details: Our preschool provides a fun and educational program for children ages 2 to 5.  In our daily program, your child participates in fun activities and builds valuable social skills.  We offer hands-on activities, from learning the alphabet to arts and crafts.

name: ABC KIDS PRESCHOOL & CHILDCARE
details: It is our mission to offer a high quality, educational preschool and childcare center to parents and their children. It is our belief that children learn best through play and experience while in a safe, loving, and supportive environment. Offering this nurturing environment is our primary goal. Children will learn self-help, social, and educational skills while the teachers work to serve each child's individual needs.

name: ABC LEARNING MONTESSORI, LLC
details: ABC Learning Montessori believes that each child is a unique individual who needs a secure, loving and stimulating atmosphere in which to grow and mature emotionally, intellectually, physically, and socially. We acknowledge that children develop, grow, and learn in different ways and at different rates. ABC Learning Montessori respects and supports the individual needs and talents of its students and seeks to empower each student to reach his/her fullest potential.

name: ALCOTT PRESCHOOL
details: Our school gives each student the opportunity to learn with an individualized focus, an advantage of our small and intimate size. Our dedicated staff works to create a school environment that helps students thrive. All students receive extra science, physical education and choral music each week. Plus we offer a variety of after-school opportunities including art, science, Spanish -- and one of the only elementary schools in the city teaching German

name: ALL ABOARD PRESCHOOL
details: We believe that God created each child unique in their needs, interests, personalities, gifts, talents, learning styles and development. Teachers carefully observe students in order to customize the curriculum and individualize lesson plans, based on instructional goals for each child.

name: ALPINE CHILDREN'S ACADEMY
details: Alpine Children's Academy helps your child become their very best by fulfilling childhood milestones and advancing them developmentally.

name: ALTURAS INTEGRATED STATE PRESCHOOL
details: We are a part day school, and our mission at the Alturas Elementary State Preschool is to provide quality education to children ages three to five years old. Each child is unique.  We strive to plan our environment and curriculum to meet their individual needs.  We believe that children are lifelong learners and we provide the opportunities for children to grow and develop their social, emotional, cognitive, physical and creative skills, through planned and purposeful play.   We respect the diversity, culture and values of each family, and by collaborating with other community agencies, we are able to offer continued assistance, education and support.

name: ANAHEIM DISCOVERY CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL
details: We believe that Anaheim Discovery Christian School was established by the Holy Spirit and exists to provide Spiritual and academic development for students, staff, parents, guardians and the school community. The Anaheim Discovery Christian School believes that each student was created by God with unique, individual gifts to ultimately be developed and used for God’s ordained purpose in life.  Our faculty’s primary purpose is to be an example of Christ like behavior so that each child will commit his or her life to Him.

name: ANAHEIM ELEMENTARY SCHOOL DISTRICT-PALM LANE
details: At Palm Lane, we believe in a progressive, relevant, well-rounded education. Every child has music, project-based learning and educational technology integrated with the common core standards for a leading edge learning experience. We also have a dual language academy for families who choose the path of biliteracy.

name: APPLESEEDS ACADEMY
details: Appleseeds Academy was created by Leigh-Ellen Yarbrough (Lulu) who has over 20 years of experience in education and holds a MAED in Educational Leadership.

name: ATCAA JAMESTOWN EARLY HEAD START
details: We are committed to helping our local residents become self-reliant and supported by our community. There are many trusted community partners (government, non-profit, faith-based,educational) in our area who may provide you additional assistance. If there is something that we can not help you with, we will do our best to refer you to who can.

name: ATCAA SONORA HEAD START
details: We are committed to helping our local residents become self-reliant and supported by our community. There are many trusted community partners (government, non-profit, faith-based,educational) in our area who may provide you additional assistance. name: AUBURN'S HOUSE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
details: Auburn’s House Montessori School has provided quality education on the Monterey Peninsula since 1986. The Velasquez’s are a respected family in the community that has always strived to create an environment that promotes the love of learning.

name: BARRY PRESCHOOL
details: Barry Elementary School is an extension of our community; rich in tradition, respectful and responsible to our environment, receptive to the opinions, and beliefs of the diverse cultures we serve.The shared decision-making of our staff, parents, students and community members provides a school setting that is safe, conducive to learning,fosters a family atmosphere, promotes school and self-pride and encourages children to continue to learn throughout their lives.

name: BCSD/HORT ELEMENTARY PRE-KINDERGARTEN
details: Hort Elementary has be providing academic services for many years.  Before it adopted the name “Hort” in 1956, it was known as Hawthorne School.  The school was named after Fred Hort and his wife Ovillah. Fred Hort worked with the city schools for 21 years, including roles as storekeeper and assistant purchasing agent.  Ovillah Hort taught in many schools in Bakersfield from 1910 to 1955.  She helped establish the first hot-lunch program and was active in the first parent-teacher association in Bakersfield.  We are proud to have such a rich heritage, and everyday the staff continues the valiant efforts of Mr. and Mrs. Hort to provide excellence and innovation in education for each of its students.

name: BEAMER STATE PRESCHOOL
details: Beamer Park Elementary School staff provides our students with a challenging, high quality, standards-based learning program that empowers them to become critical thinkers, scholars, productive citizens and leaders within a diverse, multicultural community

name: BERGAMO MONTESSORI AT SERRANO
details: We are a group of inspired educators with a common vision to provide a unique educational experience for children. Our teachers, however, are just one part of the community that includes students, parents and staff. During these formative years of your child’s life, our community provides support, friendship and guidance in accordance with Montessori principles of respect and peace.

name: BORIS PRESCHOOL CUSD
details: The 6 C’s- critical thinking, communication, creativity, collaboration, character, and citizenship are incorporated into every aspect of the learning environment. Our classrooms are flexible spaces where personalized learning strategies are developed and used based on student needs.

name: BOYS & GIRLS CLUBS OF GARDEN GROVE EARLY CHILDHOO
details: The mission of Boys & Girls Clubs of Garden Grove is to enable all young people, especially those who need us most, to reach their full potential as productive, caring, responsible citizens.

name: BRIGHT HORIZONS @USC ALCAZAR CHILD DEV. CTR
details: Welcome! This is an exciting stage in your child’s early education, and our talented team of caring teachers is here to inspire learning, encourage confidence, and nurture your child's growth and development. Our World at Their Fingertips curriculum features an arts program that sparks creativity, a language program that fosters an interest in reading, a science program that stimulates curiosity, and more. There’s always something new to explore. And our convenient location, schedules that accommodate your busy workday, and an open-door policy make it easy to stay involved. Visit us and come see what we’re all about!

name: BRIGHT LITTLE MINDS PRESCHOOL & DAYCARE
details: Bright Little Minds Montessori Preschool & Daycare is dedicated to the education, healthy growth and care of children.

name: BRIGHT SCHOLARS ACADEMY
details: Ever since 2000, Bright Scholars Academy has been providing students with a rich and diverse learning environment. Our unparalleled teaching methods help to launch students into the successful future they have always dreamed of. We always encourage both staff and students to grow, learn and create each passing day.

name: BRIGHTER DAYS MONTESSORI SCHOOL, LLC
details: After 41 wonderful years, full of love, learning and a lifetime of fabulous memories, Brighter Days Montessori School has changed ownership and now is called Brighter Days Montessori LLC.The new owner will continue on with a tradition of the values and caring that we're created from my passion for education and nurturing young children.

name: BUILDING BLOCKS PRESCHOOL
details: I offer quality childcare and preschool. I obtain an A.S in Early Childhood Education,CPR/First Aid certification, & eight years teaching experience

name: BUSHNELL WAY ELEMENTARY
details: Bushnell Way Elementary is a public, neighborhood school serving about 230 students in the Hermon Community, just north of Downtown Los Angeles.   We provide quality education within a nurturing environment.  In addition to focusing on high academic standards, students learn compassion and respect for diversity.

name: BUTTERFLIES ACADEMY, INC
details: At Butterflies Academy preschool we understand that getting ready for the future begins at birth. The first 5 years of a child’s life is the prime time for creating a strong foundation for all future—formal and informal—learning.  It is a period of incredible growth in all areas of a child’s development.

name: CABRILLO MONTESSORI SCHOOL INC
details: At the Montessori School of Silicon Valley, our vision of “Children First, Always” inspires us to provide a rich educational experience for the whole child.Classrooms are designed to stimulate growth, providing a warm and accepting environment in which every child feels secure, respected and loved.

name: CAMPUS DOWNTOWN, INC., THE
details: Welcome to The Campus Downtown Preschool and Child Care Center. Our 14,000 square foot state of the art facility is located in the heart of downtown Stockton. Here at The Campus our focus is on early childhood development with a half day curriculum based program for ages 18 months to 6 years old. We also offer an extended care program for parents needing full time care. We truly believe every child is capable of greatness. The Campus Downtown has made it our mission to begin building and fostering the strong foundation your child will need in kindergarten and beyond.

name: CAPC - NEW VISION
details: New Vision High School provides a variety of opportunities for students to experience individual success. It is our goal to provide a quality education for every child every day

name: CAPE ALMOND CENTER
details: Community Association for Preschool Education, Inc. (CAPE, Inc.) is a non-profit organization that provides comprehensive early care and education through Head Start, Early Head Start, and State Preschool programs to children ages 0-5 in Eastern Alameda County, Early Head Start services in Central Alameda County through child care partnerships, and Medi-Cal certified Mental Health Services in Eastern, Central, and Southern Alameda County.

name: CARDEN HALL

name: CCFC - CLEO WALLACE CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER

Our programs put children at the center of an interconnected circle of families, teacher and the community.

name: CDR - OAK VIEW CENTER
details: The Oak View Park and Resource Center is a 4.27 acre space in the heart of Oak View with many services for all ages. There are numerous buildings that house a County Library and various non-profit tenants and a large enough green space that includes a variety of playground equipment, youth sports fields and park land. We also have 2 multipurpose rooms than can hold 20- 250 people that is available for rent for fundraisers, performance, private parties and group seminars.  Attached to our auditorium is a beautifully remodeled community kitchen which can be rented for cooking classes catering and eve Today, the Oak View Park and Resource Center is a success story of a "community Works!"

name: CDR - PLEASANT VALLEY HEAD START

To be eligible you must live in the area and meet low-income guidelines. To apply for either the Head Start or Early Head Start program, please visit our enrollment office at 221 E. Ventura Boulevard in Oxnard, California or by calling 805.485.7878.

From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.

From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.

name: CHILDREN'S PARADISE, INC. - PRESCHOOL
details: Using more than 25 years of experience, our infant, preschool and school-age programs are designed using the latest cutting edge, research-based educational tools and curriculum, all within a warm and home-like atmosphere. Our staff is also involved in on-going training and research in early childhood development to ensure your child is learning and developing using the latest research and techniques. We take pride in the learning program we have designed with the support of the California Department of Education and would enjoy answering any questions that you have about our program.

name: CHINATOWN COMMUNITY CHILDREN'S CENTER-NORTH BEACH
details: Our mission is to prepare children for Kindergarten and beyond by promoting educational achievement, ensuring household economic stability and strengthening cultural identity.

name: CLAIRE'S MONTESSORI INTL ACADEMY (PS)
details: We believe that each child is unique and should be treated with respect as an intelligent individual. Our primary goal is to give your child every opportunity to build self-esteem in a successful school environment and acquire a positive attitude towards learning. The Montessori concept of education allows children to experience the joy of learning at an early age and provides an environment in which intellectual, moral, creative, physical and social growth flourish.

name: CLOVIS CHRISTIAN SCHOOLS, LLC
details: Our mission is to partner with parents in the educational journey of their child.  Early learning years are the foundation for building strong connections to the world and those in it.  Our elementary school provides a safe and confident learning environment where children are encouraged to take risks, ask questions and develop strong skills that build upon one another.  Children should and will be given many opportunities to experience learning in a tangible and developmentally appropriate way for their age and developmental stage.  We honor the fact that parents are the first teachers of children and it is through our partnership that your child and family will have a wonderful learning experience.

name: COALICION DE LATINOS AMERICANOS, INC.
details: CODELA is a non-profit organization that provides a developmentally appropriate service for preschool age children by encouraging and guiding the children, respecting each child as an individual and stimulating a child’s natural interest in learning. We respect and believe each child is a unique individual with the ability to construct knowledge about themselves, others, and the world around them through creative learning.

name: COLUSA PRESCHOOL LEARNING CENTER A AM/PM
details: The Mission of Children's Services is to provide coordinated child care and development services to children, parents, and providers; and to provide resources and collaboration with educational entities, health and human service agencies, and community groups serving children and families in Colusa County.

name: COMMUNITY OF ALL NATIONS - SUSD HEAD START
COMMUNITY SEEDLINGS PRESCHOOL
details: Children’s curiosity and excitement for learning help them learn “real world” connections that are personal and meaningful to them.  This is learned through play, small group projects, dialogue, journaling, reflection, documentation, and exploration the love of learning begins through art, science, math, social studies, literacy, technology and the environments of both the indoor and outdoor classrooms.

name: COUNTRY COTTAGE PRESCHOOL
details: We are a small licensed preschool in San Luis Obispo, enrolling children ages 2 to 5 years old. Please call or email to schedule a tour of our program!

details: Early care and education services are provided within CCCI center-based programs and within CCCI’s Family Child Care Network of licensed providers who offer high quality, early learning experiences in a home-like environment.

details: Early care and education services are provided within CCCI center-based programs and within CCCI’s Family Child Care Network of licensed providers who offer high quality, early learning experiences in a home-like environment.

details: Early care and education services are provided within CCCI center-based programs and within CCCI’s Family Child Care Network of licensed providers who offer high quality, early learning experiences in a home-like environment.

Children have the opportunity to spend time observing or they may actively participate. Both are vital to learning and understanding and both are supported by center staff

name: DANIEL WEBSTER ELEMENTARY
details: Through the program PBIS, which stands for Positive Behavior Intervention System, our Daniel Webster community engages in ROAR. These are the positive expectations and behavior that help keep our school a safe and fun place to learn. Students are able to earn Leopard Loot for being Responsible, On Time, Always Safe, and Respectful in the hallways, library, cafeteria, playground, and many more

name: DAR-UL-MADINAH
details: In every era, Allah  عزوجل  sent such holy personalities to the Ummah of His beloved and blessed Prophet (May Peace and blessing of Allah be upon him) who excellently fulfilled the responsibility of calling people towards righteousness and preventing them from misdeeds. These righteous saints inculcated in other Muslims the mindset that: I must strive to reform myself and the people of the entire world. One of such great personalities is Shaykh-e-Tariqat Amir-e-Ahl-e-Sunnat ‘Allamah Maulana Abu Bilal Muhammad Ilyas Attar Qadiri Razavi Ziyaee who launched the Madani campaign of Dawat-e-Islami, a global & non-political movement for the preaching of Quran and Sunnah, with the help of some of his companions in Karachi, Pakistan in Zul-Qa’da-tul-Haram 1401 A.H. (September, 1981). He is a symbol of past saints in attributes, like fear of Allah, deep devotion to the beloved Prophet, zeal and determination for following Quran & Sunnah, for reviving Sunnah, piety, forgiveness, perseverance, patience, thankfulness, humility, simplicity, sincerity, asceticism, good manners, absolute disinterest in the world, concern about the protection of faith, ambition to spread religious knowledge and reforming the Muslims.

name: DCCNS
details: DCCNS is a non-profit, parent co-operative preschool staffed by certified, early childhood teachers who provide a planned, developmentally appropriate, hands-on curriculum. DCCNS offers varied play environments and continuous social experiences as a means of teaching and conveying important skills for school readiness

name: DELIBERATE CREATIONS CHILD DEV.CTR/HEAVENLYVISION
details: Every child is unique and we believe that success and growth come from encouragement and praise. Our teachers focus on building every child’s self esteem and confidence through positive feedback and rewards. We nurture their natural strengths. A child see’s the world around them with wonder and awe, we believe in encouraging their natural curiosity.

name: DIAMOND COVE II - SUSD HEAD START
DUCKS NEST - 41ST STREET
details: Our unique preschool environment is designed to support and encourage your child’s natural curiosity and enthusiasm for learning. With locations in Berkeley and Oakland, our schools provide child-sized nooks and crannies integrated into a complex of bright classrooms, play areas, and an oasis of beautiful gardens, flowers, and sandboxes.

name: E CENTER HS PGMS - MOSS CENTER
details: Migrant Seasonal/Migrant Early Head Start provides quality childcare services free of cost to low income families that work in agriculture related work such as; working in produce fields, produce canning, and packing plants.

name: EARLY LEARNING ACADEMY-WINIFRED PIFER
details: he Winifred Pifer staff is skilled and dedicated in meeting the academic and social needs of each student. Your child's education is our top priority. We have nearly 450 enthusiastic students in grades preschool to fifth grade. Each day we look forward to providing all students a meaningful,  motiviating and well-rounded curriculum that ensures your child will have success.

name: EAST BAY WALDORF SCHOOL
details: The Waldorf curriculum offers a true and tested alternative education, especially suited to families who desire a strong intellectual and aesthetic foundation for their children, but who also wish to allow their children the opportunity to fully experience the joys of childhood without premature academic pressures. The East Bay Waldorf School can offer you and your children a community of teachers, parents, and students who strive to build creative lives that are filled with meaning.

name: EDISON LANGUAGE ACADEMY PRESCHOOL
details: Edison is a warm and diverse community and focuses on the development of the whole child. We are fortunate to have a supportive and involved parent community with over 200 trained parent volunteers who support our programs and students in many different ways. Please do whatever you can to support your child’s school with your time, talents, and resources! It takes a village to give our children this kind of education and there’s a place where everyone can make a comfortable contribution.

name: EDNA BEAMAN ELEMENTARY PRESCHOOL
details: Edna Beaman Elementary School is a preschool-5th grade school located in a rural, isolated, southeast corner of Mono County on Highway 6.  This year the school has an enrollment of approximately 31 students and is one of four elementary school sites in the Eastern Sierra Unified School District.  With such a small enrollment, Edna Beaman is able to offer a more "one-on-one" teacher-student environment than other surrounding schools.

name: EDSPERIENCE CDC, THE
details: Our goal at The EdSperience is to ensure that every child is taught and gains the most enriching academic experience a center can offer. We focus on the whole child in an effort to promote healthy lifestyles, a safe, loving environment, actively engaged students, a supportive, caring staff, and an academically challenging curriculum. Our school educates children 2-6 years of age. Our goal is to ensure that every student who leaves The EdSperience is working at least one grade level above state standard. Students learn at their own pace and all work is individualized to fit each child’s specific academic needs

name: ELM PARK PRESCHOOL
details: Incoming students are observed and/or informally assessed; progress is monitored throughout the year.  Elm Park strives to prepare students for the Poway Unified School District while also encouraging the child's natural love of learning in a warm, nurturing environment.  Children thrive in our small classes geared for kindergarten readiness.

name: EMPRIEL LEARNING ACADEMY
details: Empriel Learning Academy serves children between the ages of two and five years old. We also provide care for toddlers as young as 18 months and and tutoring for children as old as 12 years of age.

name: EVERGREEN MONTESSORI SCHOOL - AR
details: Our mission is to create an environment for facilitating the unfolding of the human potential. We provide an educational environment that fosters an enthusiasm for learning and encourages children to reach their fullest potential. We strive to provide the highest quality Montessori education available; emphasizing basic academic disciplines and promoting the development of independence, self- respect, and respect for others

name: EXPLORING MINDS MONTESSORI HAZELTINE
details: Exploring Minds Montessori Preschool provides a developmentally-based learning environment on the teachings of Dr. Maria Montessori. The Montessori philosophy and materials are designed to support and engage the natural curiosity and growth of the whole child.

name: FAITH CHAPEL LEARNING ACADEMY
details: Faith Chapel Learning Academy is centrally located in Spring Valley, serving all families around San Diego county. Our focus is centered around teaching children who God is and how much he loves them – all while they explore reading, physical education, art, music and science. Our Learning to Read program will introduce your children to the basic fundamentals of reading. Our teachers will work with each student individually at their own pace in order to make reading a success.

name: FELTON LEARNING CENTER
details: Felton’s early childhood educators are trained in and implement The Creative Curriculum for Infant, Toddler and Preschool. This nationally recognized play-based curriculum is designed to help children develop their social competence, positive approach to learning, and the pre-academic skills needed to succeed as learners

name: FLORIDA STREET DISCOVERY CENTER
details: Each day we are excited to see that students come to school ready to learn and work hard. We thank the families for partnering with us to ensure the children have a rich, well-rounded academic foundation. We commit to cherish, protect, and educate our students while maintaining an environment of high standards for academics and citizenship.

name: FRENCH MONTESSORI PRESCHOOL OF SAN DIEGO, THE
details: The Montessori teaching method encourages children to develop strong independence, concentration, and order skills. In our preschool, children learn how to be self-directed by providing a prepared environment where they choose their own work, based on their own interests. Montessori materials promote positive attitude towards school, self-confidence, sense of order, and habit of concentration.

name: FUSD-MOUNTAIN VISTA PRE SCHOOL
details: Mountain Vista Elementary School is committed to providing a safe, respectful and supportive environment. We strive to have our staff, parents, and community members actively involved in our students' learning.

name: FUSD-PIRU PRE SCHOOL
details: Piru Elementary School is a proud recipient of an Apple grant through the White House ConnectED initiative. By giving students access to the latest technology and powerful learning tools, we’re working to transform the classroom into a place of deeper exploration and creativity. Together, we can unlock the potential of the world’s future inventors, dreamers, and leaders.

name: FUSD-RIO VISTA PRE SCHOOL
details: At Rio Vista we have amazing students, wonderful teachers and supportive parents.  We strive to create a joyful learning environment where students can thrive.  Parents are always welcome to stop by, volunteer, or ask questions.  Go Roadrunners!

name: GAN YAFFA CHILDREN CENTER
details: A school with a great commitment to every child!

name: GCC UPSTREET PRESCHOOL
details: We recognize that education not only implies academics and physical skills development but also social and emotional growth. We appreciate the diversity of our families and celebrate each child's unique qualities. As we work with families to benefit children, we intend that this devotion, respect and understanding be evident in the school on a daily basis. Our teachers are committed to working with parents to achieve the best possible results for their child. We are a developmental school with an emphasis on age appropriate academics. Areas of academic importance include: early learning skills in math, language, art and science. We provide each child with the necessary foundation for school readiness. In addition to academics - social and emotional well-being also plays a significant role in a child's development. Our curriculum, various activities, and daily experiences provide children with opportunities for a fun, enriching and exciting time while they build relationships.

name: GENIUS KIDS - PLEASANTON BERNAL
details: At Genius Kids, our advanced accelerated learning programs are designed to meet each child’s individual development needs. Our curriculum has been recognized worldwide for its emphasis in leadership, public speaking and personality development.

name: GGA KIDS MARIN
details: GGA Kids Marin provides quality early childhood education for the community of Marin County through a stimulating, loving, Christian environment and a curriculum of active learning that nurtures the growth of the whole child. It is our purpose to prepare each child for the next level of learning and growing cognitively, emotionally, socially, and physically.

name: GOOD SHEPHERD CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL
details: We think nurturing the minds of children is the most honorable and rewarding job. Caring and educating the future is like planting and growing a tree. We hope to let the roots sink in deep and grow tall like a tree planted by streams of water. Someday we believe the children will give back to the world what they have received through their life.

name: GRACE ACADEMY
details: We here at Grace Academy Christian Preschool believe that children respond and navigate best in their own age appropriate environment. Young children learn play introduced through intellectual challenges, positive self-esteem through age appropriate curriculum and hands on science explorations. Young children need the implementation of discovery at their own pace, having the option to be creative in their own way while given ample and appropriate choices and experiences. When scaffolding these elements into the building of each child, age appropriate learning is accomplished. When combined with developmentally sound curriculum and excellent teaching staff, children are allowed the freedom to develop at their pace

name: GRACE CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL
details: Grace Christian Preschool is designed to pave the way for children to have a jump start towards a bright and successful future through the power of God's love. Through Faith,Love,and Patience,we will Teach,Honor,Respect and Responsibility. Planting seeds of Godly character and producing children of integrity. As our program is centered around this theme,we infuse our children with the knowledge that with God ALL PROBLEMS can be managed and all dreams can be achieved.

name: GREAT ADVENTURES LEARNING CENTER, INC.
details: Great Adventures Learning Center holds to the philosophy that all facets of a child's personality (social, intellectual, spiritual, physical and emotional) are inter-related, and school must provide the opportunity for the natural unfolding of the mind, personality and capacities of the child.

name: HAPPY BIRCH PRESCHOOL- TAMARIND
details: We believe each child possesses miraculous abilities and unique forms of intelligence. Our project based approach is built upon children’s interests, which we discover through observation as well as reflection between teachers, children and parents. This focus on children’s unique ideas empowers them on their life-long journey to become self-motivated problem solvers.

name: HAPPY HEARTS PRESCHOOL
details: appy Hearts Preschool Program is child-centered, with a play-based philosophy.  We believe children learn through active exploration in an environment that is rich in materials and provides opportunities to converse, socialize, work, play and negotiate with others.  Our classrooms are planned to encourage curiosity, exploration and problem solving.  We believe that purposeful play is the true work of the child.  Through this play we view children as thinkers reflecting about their world.

name: HAPPY TIMES CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
details: Happy Times Child Development Center staff will strive to provide quality childcare, ensure the safety and well being of each child in our program and provide educational services that promotes and enhance each child's growth and development. We believe that every child is unique and are committed to providing a safe and nurturing environment and meeting the needs of each child to the best of our ability. A positive attitude and a loving atmosphere are emphasized in each classroom. We praise each child's development and promote self-pride as they grow into each development.

name: HARVEST HILL STEAM ACADEMY CDC
details: The District is offering a new TK through 6th grade program at Harvest Hill STEAM Academy beginning in 2018/19. This program will expand to a TK thru 8th grade program in the 2020/21 school year. All current 5th grade students living within the HHSA boundaries will attend HHSA next year unless they have an approved Intra-District Transfer request to attend Bell Mountain Middle School or another middle school in the District. The new HHSA program also offers the opportunity for families who live within any of the Districts middle school boundaries to request an Intra-District Transfer to have their current 5th grader attend HHSA next year.

name: HAZEL'S CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL&CHILD CARE CENTER II
details: Welcome to Hazels Christian Preschool & Childcare Center, a progressive all year-round preschool providing Modesto and its environs families with a child-focused approach to early childhood learning, christian environment , collaborative family atmosphere, and a safe, inspiring environment that encourages exploration and creativity.

name: HAZEL GOES COOK ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Hazel Goes Cook School’s mission is to empower students to become responsible global citizens and lifelong learners. We are committed to fostering students to become inquiring, knowledgeable, and caring participants in a diverse, multicultural, democratic society through quality education and high expectations. Our students will be prepared with the knowledge and compassion to equip them with the expertise to be globally active leaders of the 21st century

name: HEAD START - KAWANA
details: The ELC includes Head Start, State Preschool operated by North Bay Children's Center (NBCC), and district-operated special education programs. These programs provide opportunities for children ages 3-5 for full-day, part-day and specially-designed instructional programs. In addition, the ELC outdoor classroom is equipped with age-appropriate play structures and spaces that facilitate and support early learning.

name: HEAD START - MARTIN LUTHER KING JR
HEBREW ACADEMY
details: At the Hebrew Academy Huntington Beach, pre-school through grade twelve students develop a deep love of learning in both general and Judaic studies. Our dedicated staff, teachers, and warm, welcoming community help to provide a nurturing, yet challenging environment that encourages all students to reach their full potential in order to act as self-confident, responsible citizens with a strong connection to their Judaism and community.

name: HERITAGE CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL
details: Heritage Christian School is established as an independent private Christian school in Orange County to provide an excellent educational experience based on the authoritative and inerrant Word of God. The goal is to facilitate the development of the student spiritually, academically, physically, emotionally, and socially; All for the Glory of God

name: HERITAGE CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL EAST CAMPUS
details: Heritage Christian School’s mission is to provide a challenging program of academic excellence from a Biblical point of view partnering with parents to equip their children with a firm spiritual foundation while impacting the world for Christ.

name: HERITAGE CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL NORTH CAMPUS
details: Heritage Christian School’s mission is to provide a challenging program of academic excellence from a Biblical point of view partnering with parents to equip their children with a firm spiritual foundation while impacting the world for Christ.

name: HERITAGE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
details: Heritage Montessori grew out of a close personal and professional relationship with Dr. Maria Montessori, and our mission is, quite simply, to continue her work.  As the first montessori school in Orange County, and one of the first montessori schools in the U.S., Heritage has a unique responsibility and, with it, a unique opportunity to weave together a strong sense of community, as the legacy we embrace is shared in the lives of the teachers and families we have touched since 1962

name: HERMOSA DRIVE STATE PRESCHOOL
details: In partnership with parents and the community, Hermosa’s goal is to achieve educational excellence. Learners are inspired to become academically and socially successful in a challenging, respectful environment. Differentiated instruction is designed to address the individual needs of students. The school community promotes citizenship that fosters personal self-worth and celebrates diversity. Hermosa strives to meet the challenges of today and tomorrow.

name: HI FI PRESCHOOL
details: We believe that every child is unique and will grow at his or her own pace. Our teachers spend time nurturing children’s strengths and encouraging them to reach new heights

name: HILLSBOROUGH PRIVATE SCHOOL
details: Founded in 1968, Hillsborough has been serving families in search of an education that is both unique and dynamic. We pride ourselves on our individualized approach to teaching the whole child with an emphasis in the core subjects, character education, and the arts. Our small class sizes allow for a learning environment that nurtures independent, confident, and critical thinkers as we prepare our students for tomorrow’s world

name: HIS KIDS CHILDRENS CENTER
details: Our aim is that our children approach learning with confidence and joy, to be willing to take risks, make commitments, become involved, and be accountable for their actions.

name: HRASHQ PRESCHOOL
details: Our aim is to create a program that is engaging and responsive for every student. We strive to make learning fun by helping students accomplish challenges and exceed their goals, in a caring and supportive environment. Located in one of the world’s greatest cities, Wix.com is deeply enriched by and involved with the San Francisco community.
